articles.title: More than 150 whales stranded on remote Australian beach - BBC.com
articles.description: Though 90 of the 157 stranded whales survived, they could not be saved due to complex conditions.
articles.content:
Tiffanie Turnbull
Australian authorities are euthanising about 90 false killer whales which survived a mass stranding on a remote beach in Tasmania.
